        <!--Condition/Glossary Box-->
        <div class="Glossary">
            
            <label style="text-align: center;">Reforged Condition Glossary</label>
            
            <dl>
                
                <dt>Armor Break</dt>
                    <dd>All attacks against afflicted creature roll with +1 auto-hit die for 2 rounds (does not stack).</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Bleeding (#)</dt>
                    <dd>At the start of the  turn, take pure damage equal to the (#), then reduce the (#) total by 1. This condition has a duration
                    equal to the (#) remaining. Bleeding can stack, adding the new (#) to the previous (#) total. Can be stopped by using a Synthentic Skin
                    item (Reforged pg. 166) as an action.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Blind</dt>
                    <dd>All sight-based skill checks (Observation, Insight, Attacks, etc.) roll with 4 auto-miss dice and -4 bonus dice.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Burning/Catch Fire</dt>
                    <dd>At the start of the afflicted's turn, they take 4 + Player Level (to a Max of 15) fire damage. This damage lasts for 3 rounds and can be
                    extinguished using a channel 1 action. If a burning target would gain the Burning condition again, they immediately take 1/2 the
                    fire damage but no additional rounds are added to the original Burning condition's duration.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Confusion</dt>
                    <dd>For 3 rounds, the afflicted unit will attack the nearest creature, whether friend or foe. If multiple units are nearby, roll to
                    determine which creature will be the target and it will not target the creature who put the Confusion condition on them, unless no
                    other creatures are in range. May perform a Contested Judgement check to resist. (Duration completes at the end of your 2nd turn.)</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Darkness/Dark</dt>
                    <dd>As Blind condition.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Dim-light</dt>
                    <dd>Roll with 2 auto-miss dice and -2 bonus dice on all sight-based skill checks.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Drained</dt>
                    <dd>All outgoing healing is halved for 2 rounds. (Duration completes at the end of your 2nd turn.)</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Fall Damage</dt>
                    <dd>Most Environmental Suits have emergency air-propulsion jets implemented in them to prevent most fall damage below 6 sqs tall.
                    For every 3 sqs above this range, the target takes 1d6+6 force damage.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Fear</dt>
                    <dd>At the start of the afflicted's turn, perform a Contested Mentality/Power check against the being that afflicted the fear condition.
                    On a failure, the afflicted creature runs their Base Movement away from the square or being that cause the Fear. This does activate
                    Reactionary Strikes (Reforged pg. 23).</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Grasped</dt>
                    <dd>Upon being grasped, perform a Contested Muscle/Power check. On a failure, the afflicted creature cannot perform actions/reactions.
                    At the start of each turn, both parties must perform the previous check again. If the afflicted succeeds the check, they lose the Grasped
                    condition and may perform actions as normal.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Madness</dt>
                    <dd>Roll 1d6 and consult the following chart.</dd>
                    <dd>1 - Knocked prone in laughter for 2 rounds. Each round, the afflicted may attempt a Hard (4) Mentality check. On a success, they 
                    wake from the Madness and may act as normal.</dd>
                    <dd>2 - Immediately attack the closest unit with an auto-hit die. This attack inflicts +1d6 damage.</dd>
                    <dd>3 - Take 10% Max HP chaotic damage and for the next 3 rounds, gain an auto-miss die when standing within 8 sqs of an ally.</dd>
                    <dd>4 - For 3 rounds, all incoming healing is negated.</dd>
                    <dd>5 - Gain Blind for 2 rounds.</dd>
                    <dd>6 - Gain the Void Sickness conditon (Reforged pg. 172).</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Poison</dt>
                    <dd>At the start of the afflicted's turn, take Player Level in physical damage and roll 1d2. On a 1 result, gain Sickly; on a 2 result,
                    gain Drained.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Prone</dt>
                    <dd>Afflicted being is knocked onto their back or front and must use half movement to get back up. While prone, lose all reactions
                    and adjacent attackers roll with +1 auto-hit die when attempting to hit the afflicted being.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Sickly</dt>
                    <dd>All incoming healing is halved for 2 rounds. (Duration completes at the end of your 2nd turn.)</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Suffocating</dt>
                    <dd>Afflicted target takes 20% of their Max HP in pure damage every round. Note: most beings begin suffocating after 1 minute (10 rounds).</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Taunted</dt>
                    <dd>The Taunted target must attack the Taunting unit for 2 rounds. If the Taunted being attempts to attack anything other than the Taunting unit,
                    they must perform a Hard (4) Mentality check. On a failure, they must attack the Taunting unit.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>True Sight</dt>
                    <dd>True Sight allows the afflicted being to see all hidden objects, traps, beings, or runes/writing within sight and up to 20 sqs away.
                    Those under the effect of True Sight can never lost rack of beings in Covert while they are within sight and in range, though those beings 
                    may perform a Covert check to hide themselves from others. Additionally, those with True Sight can determine what is illusionary.</dd>
                
            </dl>
            
            <label style="text-align: center;">Prophecy Condition Glossary</label>
            
            <dl>
                
                <dt>Blessed</dt>
                    <dd>While under this condtion, gain seven D2s that may be rolled after any check or damage has been performed. The D2 result rolled may then 
                    be used as additional pips to affect the rolled check or damage dice. Only one D2 may be rolled per check.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Chaos Sickness</dt>
                    <dd>While active, take +10% additional damage from all damage types, excluding Ordic.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Discombobulated (#)</dt>
                    <dd>While active, add -1 Temporary Virtue Point to Mentality and Judgement. This may not bring either Virtue below 2 points. If you fail a 
                    Mentality or Judgement skill check while under this effect, gain the Stun condition. (Discombobulated does not stack and its duration 
                    completes at the end of your turn after the # of turns have passed.)</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Harsh Terrain</dt>
                    <dd>While moving through areas under this condition, each square requires 2 squares of movement to pass through.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Stagnated (#)</dt>
                    <dd>Those afflicted with this condition lose the ability to transform their shape from the current form they hold (outside of natural 
                    duration ends). Premium level adversaries are immune to this condition.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Suppressed</dt>
                    <dd>The Suppressed target must expend an action to move out of full cover. If they do not expend an action, the Suppressing unit 
                    automatically inflicts their weapon's damage to the Suppressed target. A Suppressed target in half cover must expend half movement 
                    each round or take half the Suppressing unit's weapon damage. Additionally, Suppressed targets roll with -1 bonus die on attacks 
                    and must use half of their movement to perform the attack. A target cannot be affected by multiple Suppressed conditions.</dd><br>
                    
                <dt>Weary (#)</dt>
                    <dd>For the duration, the afflicted being adds -2 Temporary Virtue Points to their Primary Virtue (or highest Virtue if they do not have
                    a primary Virtue).</dd><br>
                
            </dl>
            
        </div>
        
        <!--Minor/Major Injuries section-->
        <div class="Injuries">
            
